## Boolean-based blind SQLi technique:
- To extract Nth character: SUBSTRING(column, N, 1)
- ASCII value comparison: ASCII(SUBSTRING(...)) > X
- TRUE condition means 1487 bytes response, FALSE means 1484-1486

## Implementation steps:
